Title : Katit Indian Reserve No. 1
Text : '''Katit Indian Reserve No. 1''' is the main [[Indian reserve]] of the [[Wuikinuxv]] people, and is one of the three reserves governed by the [[Wuikinuxv Nation]] [[band government]].<ref>[http://pse5-esd5.ainc-inac.gc.ca/fnp/Main/Search/FNReserves.aspx?BAND_NUMBER=541&lang=eng Reserves/Settlements/Villages, Indian and Northern Affairs Canada]</ref>  It is located in [[British Columbia]], Canada, on the entrance to [[Owikeno Lake]] on the north side of the [[Wannock River]]<ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/64423.html BC Names/GeoBC entry "Katit 1 (Indian reserve)"]</ref> near to, but separate from, the non-native community and sport fishing resort of [[Rivers Inlet, British Columbia|Rivers Inlet]].  Similarly-named '''Katit Island''' is in the Wannock River at {{coord|51|40|41|N|127|11|48|W|display=inline|source:BCNames}},<ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/34807.html BC Names/GeoBC entry "Katit Island"]</ref> while '''Kahtit Creek''' is downstream, near the mouth of the Wannock River at {{coord|51|40|47|N|127|15|00|W|display=inline|source:BCNames}}<ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/27504.html BC Names/GeoBC entry "Kahtit Creek"]</ref> near the Wuikinuxv village known as [[Oweekeno]].

